Patch Set 8: Code-Review+1

This looks good but I'm wondering if we should add a test case here. I'm actually not sure whether it makes sense.

This would have been caught if we had a test case running migrations on a new/empty database. The test case we have currently uses an existing db, which is why this didn't get caught. But if we start testing every migration on new and existing databases, then it maybe a huge bloat. I'm thinking what's a better way of testing every migration on both  new and existing dbs.
